<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="D" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Dam1" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Dam,</orth> subst. female parent, used of birds: <bibl n="shak. mv 3.1.33" default="NO" valid="yes">Merch. III, 1, 33</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. mac 4.3.218" default="NO" valid="yes">Mcb. IV, 3, 218</bibl>. Of quadrupeds: <bibl n="shak. mnd 5.227" default="NO" valid="yes">Mids. V, 227</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 2h6 3.1.214" default="NO" valid="yes">H6B III, 1, 214</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 3h6 3.2.162" default="NO" valid="yes">H6C III, 2, 162</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. h8 1.1.176" default="NO" valid="yes">H8 I, 1, 176</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tit 2.3.142" default="NO" valid="yes">Tit. II, 3, 142</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tit 4.1.97" default="NO" valid="yes">IV, 1, 97</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tit 5.2.144" default="NO" valid="yes">V, 2, 144</bibl>. -- <cit><quote>The devil and his d.:</quote> <bibl n="shak. wiv 1.1.151" default="NO" valid="yes">Wiv. I, 1, 151</bibl></cit>. <bibl n="shak. wiv 4.5.108" default="NO" valid="yes">IV, 5, 108</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. err 4.3.51" default="NO" valid="yes">Err. IV, 3, 51</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. shr 1.1.106" default="NO" valid="yes">Shr. I, 1, 106</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. shr 3.2.158" default="NO" valid="yes">III, 2, 158</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. jn 2.128" default="NO" valid="yes">John II, 128</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 1h6 1.5.5" default="NO" valid="yes">H6A I, 5, 5</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tit 4.2.65" default="NO" valid="yes">Tit. IV, 2, 65</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. oth 4.1.153" default="NO" valid="yes">Oth. IV, 1, 153</bibl>.
<lb />Used of human mothers, in contempt: <bibl n="shak. tmp 1.2.320" default="NO" valid="yes">Tp. I, 2, 320</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tmp 1.2.320" default="NO" valid="yes">Tp. I, 2, 320</bibl> <bibl n="shak. tmp 3.2.109" default="NO" valid="yes">III, 2, 109</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. mv 4.1.136" default="NO" valid="yes">Merch. IV, 1, 136</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. wt 1.2.137" default="NO" valid="yes">Wint. I, 2, 137</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. wt 2.3.94" default="NO" valid="yes">II, 3, 94</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 3h6 2.2.135" default="NO" valid="yes">H6C II, 2, 135</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. cor 3.1.293" default="NO" valid="yes">Cor. III, 1, 293</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tit 5.1.27" default="NO" valid="yes">Tit. V, 1, 27</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tit 5.2.191" default="NO" valid="yes">V, 2, 191</bibl>. Used as a term of endearment: <cit><quote>blemished his gracious d.</quote> <bibl n="shak. wt 3.2.199" default="NO" valid="yes">Wint. III, 2, 199</bibl></cit>.
